				Hail. Lydl the Great spawns at the south-west corner of the zone wall in East Freeport, about every fifteen minutes real time, and walks slowly along the zone border going south to north, where he unspawns, takes a nap, and repeats. He is a bluecon to my lv 6 ENC - but I did not know about the quest, until reading here.<BR>
<BR>
I saw him while on recon, looking for the Orc Centurion [a little vendetta since he killed me once] - when this Orc Apprentice blasts me with a fire spell. Heh, this was my first meeting with an NPC caster. When he hit me I had only Strength and Shield, no pet, no haze. He blinded me three times after I got off a suffocating shere, and headed to the guards. My skin was burning, and my hair was on fire, but I did manage to kill him short of the gate. Talk about adrenalin rush! I had a bit less than one bubb HP remaining.<BR>
<BR>
Now that I know more about Lydl the Great, and my character is a lv 7, might be time for a visit, Heh.<BR>
